00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,900
=Daughter of Fortune=

2
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,460
(Adapted from the novel
"Phoenix Palace Dream" by Lan Jiujiu)

3
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:08,460
=Episode 12=

4
00:01:25,330 --> 00:01:26,599
You thought entering the palace

5
00:01:26,599 --> 00:01:28,560
would bring you wealth and glory?

6
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,890
So what if you've been granted
the title of Lady of Beauty?

7
00:01:31,079 --> 00:01:32,680
His Majesty values the Liu family.

8
00:01:33,079 --> 00:01:34,400
He won't come save you.

9
00:01:36,319 --> 00:01:37,959
The day you entered the palace,

10
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,120
I already left behind a letter

11
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,690
with one of my trusted people
in the palace.

12
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,040
It says that you and Madam Shen

13
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,959
used witchcraft

14
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:47,439
to curse His Majesty.

15
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:49,519
If you dare harm me,

16
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,640
that letter will
be delivered to His Majesty.

17
00:01:53,239 --> 00:01:54,480
The entire Shen family

18
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,079
will be buried alongside you.

19
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,519
How dare you frame me!

20
00:02:01,239 --> 00:02:02,640
It's only a letter.

21
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:05,040
With Dowager Consort Liu backing me,

22
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,359
you can't do a thing.

23
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,919
Tell me,

24
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,439
whose will arrive first?

25
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:14,439
Your letter,
or His Majesty's secret agents?

26
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:16,960
How dare you harm me!

27
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,120
Give it to me!

28
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:23,919
Back then, my mother and I
had Father's favor all to ourselves.

29
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,960
It was your mother,

30
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,400
with no sense of shame,

31
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:29,080
who seduced Father.

32
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:31,390
That was because he
himself was fickle and unfaithful.

33
00:02:31,479 --> 00:02:33,039
How can you blame my mother for that?

34
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:34,159
You still dare talk back?

35
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:40,199
Do you really think
His Majesty cares about you?

36
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:43,520
You've been locked up here
for an entire day,

37
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,479
yet His Majesty hasn't even

38
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:47,240
asked about you once.

39
00:02:47,599 --> 00:02:50,479
Shen Zhinian, just accept your fate.

40
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:53,280
No one cares whether you live or die.

41
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:54,840
To me,

42
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:57,759
you will always be nothing
more than an ant beneath my feet.

43
00:02:58,039 --> 00:02:58,639
Bah!

44
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,590
Carry out the tattoo punishment.

45
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:34,940
♪Moon sets on palace walls,
breeze hits the gates♪

46
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:40,479
♪One glance led me
astray for half a lifetime♪

47
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,159
Your Majesty!

48
00:03:41,479 --> 00:03:42,919
Shen Zhinian seduced another man

49
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:44,080
and behaved immorally.

50
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:48,280
I acted under
the Dowager Consort's decree.

51
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:01,879
Shen Nanqiao,

52
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,479
receive the tattoo punishment

53
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,790
and be expelled from the palace.

54
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,080
Your Majesty, spare me!

55
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,560
Your Majesty, spare me!

56
00:04:08,439 --> 00:04:09,319
Your Majesty!

57
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:11,759
Your Majesty, spare me!

58
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,000
Your Majesty!

59
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:20,260
♪Time silently scars those left behind♪

60
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:23,860
♪I walk through the palace
day and night, just for my beloved♪

61
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:26,000
♪All my tenderness is for you,
I'd stay alone for you♪

62
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,279
Your Majesty, spare me!

63
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:28,439
Your Majesty!

64
00:04:32,399 --> 00:04:35,040
Young Lady only left
the Cold Palace to save me.

65
00:04:35,199 --> 00:04:37,000
She happened to run into Lady Liu

66
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:39,879
and begged Her Ladyship to save me.

67
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,199
Luckily, I tasted that dish first.

68
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,700
Otherwise, the one poisoned
would've been Young Lady.

69
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,759
Go back and rest first.

70
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:52,959
Yes.

71
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,399
Your Majesty.

72
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,319
Weren't you quite capable?

73
00:05:06,199 --> 00:05:08,439
They hit you, yet you didn't fight back?

74
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:11,120
I'm already injured like this.

75
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:15,600
Besides, how many people
could I fight alone?

76
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:18,079
I don't have anyone
powerful enough to protect me.

77
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,720
That sharp tongue of yours

78
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:21,800
is only used against me.

79
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,240
Today, you saved me.

80
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,720
I'll remember it.

81
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,839
What do you mean "you" and "me"?

82
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,360
How impudent.

83
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,720
Your Majesty treats me well,

84
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:40,959
so naturally I dare to be bold.

85
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,879
Your Majesty,

86
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,839
come a little closer.

87
00:05:49,639 --> 00:05:50,920
I have something to say.

88
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:02,000
I...

89
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,240
wish to ask Your Majesty for something.

90
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,480
What is it?

91
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:09,759
The people in this palace
are treacherous.

92
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,279
I'm afraid

93
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,759
that one day I may offend someone again.

94
00:06:14,959 --> 00:06:17,680
Your Majesty cannot stay
by my side at all times.

95
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,319
So I wish

96
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,879
to ask Your Majesty

97
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:22,680
for a death-exemption medal.

98
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,279
Do you know who
death-exemption medals are given to?

99
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:28,480
They're awarded to those who rendered
great service in supporting the ruler,

100
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,759
or saved the ruler's life.

101
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:33,120
I know.

102
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:34,959
In the future,

103
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:36,680
I will surely

104
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,639
risk life and limb for Your Majesty,

105
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,319
shield you from blades and swords,

106
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,120
and brave any danger for you.

107
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,040
Let's wait until you've recovered first.

108
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:47,959
Yes.

109
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:55,639
How could His Majesty leave so suddenly?

110
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:56,800
Now that the treatment's
been interrupted,

111
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,260
who knows whether it can
still be cured properly?

112
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:59,360
The situation was urgent.

113
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,690
There was truly no other choice.

114
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,890
Just do your best, Physician Lu.

115
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:04,680
Your Majesty, those words are mistaken.

116
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:07,079
I accepted the late Consort's
request to care for Your Majesty.

117
00:07:07,079 --> 00:07:08,439
If I fail to cure Your Majesty,

118
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:11,000
then I can only
repay my crime with death.

119
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:12,759
With all the time you're wasting talking,

120
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,510
the needles could already be in place.

121
00:07:23,199 --> 00:07:24,759
Who would've thought that one day,

122
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:26,560
Your Majesty would risk your own life

123
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,720
for the sake of a mere beauty.

124
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,399
She's just a defenseless woman.

125
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:31,439
If she were to die in my harem,

126
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:33,480
wouldn't that only make me
seem incompetent?

127
00:07:36,759 --> 00:07:37,639
It's over.

128
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,279
Everything's over.

129
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,560
Now both His Majesty
and Dowager Consort Liu have abandoned us.

130
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,319
My future is ruined.

131
00:07:47,439 --> 00:07:48,560
All because of you.

132
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,319
Lu,

133
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:52,680
I still have a way.

134
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,720
I know where the thing

135
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,160
Duke Zhen wants most is hidden.

136
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:57,680
We can seek refuge with him.

137
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,480
What did you say?

138
00:08:06,839 --> 00:08:08,160
Then I'll trust you one more time.

139
00:08:10,839 --> 00:08:11,600
Your Majesty,

140
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,000
the shadow guards discovered

141
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,890
the whereabouts of the Chifeng Army token
at Jinsong Pavilion.

142
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:16,380
Would Your Majesty like to investigate?

143
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:17,959
Jinsong Pavilion?

144
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,079
Mm.

145
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:21,319
But Jinsong Pavilion
is a famous male escort house.

146
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,680
They only receive female guests.

147
00:08:23,199 --> 00:08:25,279
It'll be difficult for us to get in.

148
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,440
What are we going there for?

149
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,720
Why are we dressed like this?

150
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,440
It's just an auction house.

151
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,799
Help me accomplish this,

152
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,639
and I'll grant you
a death-exemption medal.

153
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:51,559
I will do everything in my power.

154
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:53,799
- Good.
- Good.

155
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,399
- Wonderful!
- Wonderful!

156
00:08:56,399 --> 00:08:58,240
There's actually
a dragon deity parade tonight.

157
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,590
I heard if you touch the dragon's head,
your wishes will come true.

158
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,320
I want to touch it.

159
00:09:03,519 --> 00:09:04,960
Business first.

160
00:09:10,159 --> 00:09:10,919
Yes.

161
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:17,919
Fine.

162
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,790
I'll indulge you this once.

163
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:20,759
Mm.

164
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,980
♪Longing turns to yearning,
twining into a red string♪

165
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,380
♪Drawing your face before my eyes♪

166
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:44,990
Not playing anymore.

167
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:50,420
♪How many twists of fate
before we finally meet♪

168
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:54,220
♪The melody drifts
across rivers and mountains♪

169
00:09:54,580 --> 00:09:57,740
♪Rowing a small boat
with you through passing years♪

170
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:02,060
♪If the scenery is beautiful,
spring won't feel far away♪

171
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:05,900
♪I only wish to dance with you
among fluttering flowers and butterflies♪

172
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:10,140
♪Picking an orchid,
pledging our love forever♪

173
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:13,180
♪Even if the road to the horizon is long,
may we still share the same moon♪

174
00:10:14,759 --> 00:10:16,440
Please, Dragon Deity, protect Handan.

175
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,799
Protect my maternal family
and keep them safe and well.

176
00:10:18,799 --> 00:10:21,460
♪Then together we'll listen
to the endless wind and snow♪

177
00:10:22,399 --> 00:10:23,200
Wait a moment.

178
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:28,240
♪As time plays like strings,
youth fades from our faces♪

179
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,279
Please, Dragon Deity, bless His Majesty

180
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:31,559
with peace and safety,

181
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,279
and may all his wishes come true.

182
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,559
Boss, give me a carp lantern.

183
00:10:56,639 --> 00:10:58,399
Alright.

184
00:11:01,759 --> 00:11:02,879
Thank you.

185
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,360
Offering this in your name.

186
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:07,190
Thank you for bringing me
to see the lanterns.

187
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:10,220
♪You do not know♪

188
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:13,580
♪The partridge's cry
is full of resentment♪

189
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,000
Look!

190
00:11:17,159 --> 00:11:18,600
The sky lanterns are rising.

191
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:20,039
They're flying so high.

192
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:27,180
♪Spring breeze passes,
composing the fleeting years♪

193
00:11:27,540 --> 00:11:33,980
♪Clouds on Mount Wu,
no sails on the sea♪

194
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:41,180
♪Wanting to fold my heart
into a paper kite♪

195
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:46,000
♪But the ties are too tangled to sever♪

196
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:46,639
Your Majesty,

197
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,120
why are you late?

198
00:11:51,130 --> 00:11:52,790
I've been here
for quite some time already.

199
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,240
But seeing how happy Your Majesty
and Miss Shen were together,

200
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:56,840
I didn't wish to interrupt.

201
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:01,840
Miss Shen,

202
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,440
are your injuries any better?

203
00:12:03,679 --> 00:12:04,559
Much better.

204
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,320
Thank you.

205
00:12:07,919 --> 00:12:09,240
Why did this lantern go out?

206
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:12,679
It was never lit to begin with.

207
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,879
Your Majesty, today's outfit

208
00:12:20,279 --> 00:12:21,279
is certainly unique.

209
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:25,080
You sure talk a lot.

210
00:12:25,879 --> 00:12:27,039
Let's go.

211
00:12:44,420 --> 00:12:47,460
(Jin)

212
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:59,840
♪Broken dreams,
listening to the light rain♪

213
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:06,800
♪Bitter cold, bringing mist to the eyes♪

214
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,800
♪If we don't meet♪

215
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,240
♪Flowers bloom and fall in shame♪

216
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:20,960
♪If we meet again,
the peaches will be warm♪

217
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:27,760
♪Spring breeze passes,
dancing through the years♪

218
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:34,440
♪Brewing longing,
remembering past lives♪

219
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:41,640
♪Hard to meet, and just as hard to part♪

220
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:48,520
♪Who planted the beans
that grew into lotuses?♪

221
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:54,640
♪Spring breeze passes,
composing the fleeting years♪

222
00:13:55,560 --> 00:14:02,160
♪Clouds on Mount Wu,
no sails on the sea♪

223
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:09,000
♪Wanting to fold my heart
into a paper kite♪

224
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:15,720
♪But the ties are too tangled to sever♪

